Message.MsgText: ADMU8046E=ADMU8046E: The administrative agent port number specified for {0} connector is invalid, registerNode cannot continue.
Message.Explanation: Failed to register the node because the port number specified is invalid.
Message.UserResponse: Check your administrative agent serverindex.xml and find the correct port number of the connector.

Message.MsgText: ADMU0125E=ADMU0125E: Change the clock of the new node to be within {0} minutes of the clock of the deployment manager.
Message.Explanation: The addNode command failed because the clock of the new node is out of synchronization with the deployment manager.
Message.UserResponse: Change the clock of the new node to be within the specified minutes of the clock of the deployment manager.

Message.MsgText: ADMU7771E=ADMU7771E: Generic Server: {0} already running - use the "-forceGenericServerStart" to force server start!
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to start a generic server that has already been started.
Message.UserResponse: Use "stopServer.(bat|sh)" to stop the generic server, then retry the startServer command or use the "-forceGenericServerStart" option to try to force the start of the generic server.

Message.MsgText: ADMU0016I=ADMU0016I: Synchronizing configuration between node and cell.
Message.Explanation: Configuration synchronization is occurring between a node and a cell.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: ADMU8045I=ADMU8045I: Node has been successfully deregistered.
Message.Explanation: The node has been deregistered from an adminagent.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.
